import React , {Component} from 'react'; import axios from 'axios' class Pres extends Component { state={ consul:[], } componentDidMount=()=>{ axios.get("http://127.0.0.1:8000/patients/"+92+"/") .then((response)=>{ console.log(response.data.consultations) this.setState({consul:response.data.consultations, }) }) } render(){ const {consul}= this.state return(
{ consul.map(consul=>
{consul.date}

Type

{consul.type}

description

{consul.description}

{consul.prescription_fields.map(prescription_fields=>
# First Name Last Name Username
1 Mark Otto @mdo
2 Jacob Thornton @fat
3 Larry the Bird @twitter
{prescription_fields.id}
{prescription_fields.drug.scientific_name}
)}
)}
) }} export default Pres;
